t: parts sold and fulfilled by amazon | BobIsTheOilGuy
s: None the less, I would never buy ... claiming genuine parts, but, this is where I think it get's interesting A few years ago, I did buy an Aisin timing belt kit off amazon, but, it was sold and fulfilled by amazon, not some 3rd party seller. This is what gave me the reassurance that it wasn't a fake kit and why I bought it... I would've been concerned had I bought it off third party, but being straight from amazon I wasn't. So the question is, can we even trust brand name partsÂ ...

t: r/Honda on Reddit: Do you recommend buying parts from Amazon?
s: August 20, 2024 - Third party or aftermarket parts are fine, if you verify that you get the genuine article. I've bought brake parts on Amazon for probably a decade. Just got Akebono pads for my Type R on their a couple months ago. ... Depends on the brand. A lot of times it's half the price on Amazon.
